                <Gloss>honeycomb</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>This word is found as a variant reading only: οἱ δὲ ἐπέδωκαν αὐτῷ … ἀπὸ μελισσίου κηρίου ‘and they gave him … some honeycomb’ {S:04202404200014} (apparatus); see {D:4.50}. In rendering κηρίον it is important to employ an expression which will include both the honey and the comb. A literal rendering of ‘honeycomb’ might refer only to the wax container without the honey, but for many languages a term meaning simply ‘honey’ also refers to the honeycomb.</Comments>
